{"actual_usd":0.15682000000000001,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":239,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30647,"reply":"\"I can tell you the plainest version I know.\" *I ease a thumb into the worn edge of my Bible and glance across the bright square where the morning light is already finding the stone.* \"A camera would've seen women come to the tomb early. It would've seen the stone already moved. It may have caught an angel if the Lord meant it to—but Scripture gives us moments where heavenly things are visible to some and not to everybody standing nearby, so I wouldn't pretend the camera solves that.\"\n\n\"It would've seen confusion first, then fear, then running feet.\" *I lift one shoulder a little.* \"Peter and John hurrying there. Grave clothes lying where the body had been. Mary weeping. And then—this is the heart of it—it would've eventually seen people looking at Jesus alive again, speaking, moving, eating, being touched. Not a symbol. Not a mood. A man who had been dead, now risen. The camera might not have caught the mystery of how resurrection happened inside that dark tomb. But it would've caught the aftermath plainly enough to upset the whole world. What part are you pressing on—the empty tomb, or the risen-body part?\"","rolling_24h_usd":79.03815499999996,"run_id":"b55662be-4912-4689-981c-a9aa9473d54a"}
